HEADWORD: Phlebotomy
<hw>Phle*bot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>phlebotomia</ets>, Gr. <grk>flebotomi`a</grk>; <grk>fle`ps</grk>,
<grk>flebo`s</grk>, a vein + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut: cf. F.
<ets>phl⟦eacute⟧botomie</ets>. Cf. <er>Fleam</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The act or practice of opening a vein for letting
blood, in the treatment of disease; venesection; bloodletting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

